Commentary Text: Boult to Stoinis, out Caught by de Kock!! All the build up, all the hype, all the talk of Boult's injury, all the talk of Stoinis doing a Hulk. And we get this. Well, well. Absolute gun delivery -- back of a length, going away, but suddenly moving back in after it pitches. Stoinis can't do much, actually he could, but doesn't. Commentary Text: Nortje to Rohit, out Caught by (sub)Lalit Yadav! IS that the moment of inspiration they needed! Lalit Yadav has brought about a moment of inspiration from outside the boundary - quite literally. A slower bouncer, released from deep within the palm, Rohit gets on his favourite hook shot, doesn't get a lot of power on it, and Lalit Yadav's fresh legs have managed to sprint in from cow corner to tumble forward and take a phenomenal catch! Pace taken off has done the trick for Delhi. For now. They have an opening. That's the end of Rohit. Rohit c (sub)Lalit Yadav b Nortje 68(51) [4s-5 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Ashwin to Rohit, out Suryakumar Yadav Run Out! That's the ultimate sacrifice from Surya. Rohit has punched this one off the backfoot and taken off for the run, screams at Surya to start running, and Surya is adamant there's no run. In the end, the throws goes to the striker's end to get Rohit out, and Surya just ambles out of his crease, crossing over and making the utlimate sacrifice. Extra pressure on the MI captain, to ensure that the sacrifice was worth it. Not a lot of emotion shown by Surya, who walks back gallantly, but Rohit looks furious - whether it is with himself or with Surya, we will never know. Honestly, there was no run in that... Suryakumar Yadav run out (Praveen Dubey/Pant) 19(20) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Stoinis to de Kock, out Caught by Pant!! Gee, there's something about this guy, Stoinis. He comes in and bowls a gentle back of a length delivery close to off and has managed to force a false shot from de Kock. Looked like the off-cutter, de Kock tried to use the pace and play the late cut but the ball was too close to the stumps and a healthy edge went to the left of Pant. Big celebration from Stoinis. DC needed this to lift themselves. de Kock c Pant b Stoinis 20(12) [4s-3 6s-1]
